text: Divari (, also Romanized as Dīvārī) is a village in Holunchekan Rural District in the Central District of Qasr-e Qand County, Sistan and Baluchestan Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, its population was 47, distributed amongst nine families. == References == Category:Populated places in Qasr-e Qand County
title: Divari
